Environment Preparation & Dependency Installation:
Open your terminal or command prompt application and run the following commands sequentially to download the codebase and install the required library infrastructure.
1. Clone the repository from GitHub
git clone [https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git](https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git)

2. Navigate directly into your project root directory
cd your-repo-name

3. Install the Core Streamlit Framework and Official Google GenAI SDK
pip install streamlit google-genai

To allow the backend engine to communicate with the model cluster, configure a secure developer key:

* Navigate to Google AI Studio.
* Authenticate with a standard Google account.
* Click Get API Key in the sidebar panel.
* Click Create API Key, copy the generated alphanumeric token string, and keep it safe.

4. Fire up the application server framework on your local machine using this command:
    python -m streamlit run app.py
